								<a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/06/14/world/science-health-world/mystery-pig-virus-origins-sparks-concern/">
									<img src="https://cdn.japantimes.2xx.jp/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/p20-pig-a-20140615-200x200.jpg" alt="Mystery over pig virus origins sparks concern" title="Pig out: Scientists estimate the Porcine Epidemic Diarrhea virus has wiped out 10 percent of the U.S. pig population." />
								</a>
							</figure>
	        															<div class="content_col ">
							<header>
								<hgroup>
									<h3>
										<a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news_category/world/" class="category-link">World</a><span> / </span><a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news_category/science-health-world/" class="category-link">Science &amp; Health</a>										<span class="right date">Jun 14, 2014</span>
									</h3>
									<p><a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/06/14/world/science-health-world/mystery-pig-virus-origins-sparks-concern/">Mystery over pig virus origins sparks concern</a></p>
																			<h5 class="writer" role="author">by <a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/author/tom-polansek/" title="Posts by Tom Polansek" class="author url fn" rel="nofollow">Tom Polansek</a></h5>
																	</hgroup>
							</header>
							<p>
								Swine veterinarian Bill Minton thought the baby pigs dying at a farm in western Ohio had a bad case of gastroenteritis and was stumped when lab results came back with no indication of what had killed them.
It took nearly 30 days &#8212; and hundreds ...								<a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/06/14/world/science-health-world/mystery-pig-virus-origins-sparks-concern/" class="more_link"><span class="icon-arrow-2"></span></a>
							</p>
